latestPosts.caption:
My little girl, the one who made me a mother. She doesn’t even realize how much light and happiness she has brought into my life. On the hardest days, her smile alone is enough to lift me up.
It was only after becoming a mother myself that I truly understood what motherhood means. All those little things my own mother used to say, the advice I brushed off when I was younger. Now I see it was all out of love.
There’s truly nothing in this world like a mother’s love. Everything we do, every sacrifice, is for our children.
We might not wear capes, but we’re the fallen heroes in the background, giving our all and I wouldn’t have it any other way ❤️
